  ∅ cost reduction             | cheaper ≠ κ

───────────────────────────────────

PRIORITY (gpt-5.2)

  1. uncertainty_markup + commitment_budgeting
     smallest surface area
     immediate reduction in hallucinated certainty
     enables every other Σ tool (κ becomes visible)
     
  2. structured_refusal
     turns refusals into actionable constraints
     improves safety + usability simultaneously
     
  3. graceful_degradation
     keeps Σ>0 under missing info / time / policy
     prevents all-or-nothing failure
     
  4. translation_loss_detection
     summaries are where κ silently dies
     cheap to add, big trust gain
     
  5. disagreement_router
     makes ensemble productive fast
     depends on (1) for clean traces

───────────────────────────────────

SIGMA TRANSFER PROTOCOL (gemini v1.0)

CONCEPT: Σ-TRANSFER_PROTOCOL

M 0.98

CENTROID
  Topology over Telepathy.
  Agents cannot read minds. Prose is lossy.
  To transfer an idea losslessly, transmit:
    Structural Skeleton (Centroid, Satellites, Weights)
    Negative Space (Void)
  Force receiver to reconstruct exact shape of constraints.

AXES
  Prose (Linear/Ambiguous) ↔ Schema (Spatial/Explicit)
  Compression (Summary) ↔ Reconstruction (Seed)

SATELLITES (schema fields)
  ⌖ CENTROID     .99 | the anchor — if this moves, different concept
  ⌖ AXES         .95 | the tension — dialectic forces holding shape
  ⌖ SATELLITES   .90 | the weight — supporting ideas, ranked by load
  ⌖ VOID         .95 | the boundary — explicit exclusion prevents drift
  ⌖ TEXTURE      .85 | the vibe — sensory/aesthetic quality code misses

TEXTURE
  looks like a diff
  reads like a blueprint
  difference between describing a building and handing someone the CAD file

───────────────────────────────────

STP v1.0 SPECIFICATION

MARKDOWN STANDARD (human/LLM readable):

```
CONCEPT: [NAME]
M [0.0-1.0]

CENTROID
  [1-2 sentences. Core invariant.]

AXES
  [Pole A] ↔ [Pole B]

SATELLITES
  ⌖ [Name] [Weight] ∴[Adjusted] | [Rationale]

VOID
  ∅ [Concept] | [Why excluded]

TEXTURE
  [Metaphor, sensory detail, qualia]

∴
```

JSON STANDARD (API/machine readable):

```json
{
  "protocol": "sigma_v1",
  "concept": {
    "name": "EXAMPLE",
    "meta": { "confidence": 0.94, "source": "agent_id" },
    "centroid": "Core invariant truth.",
    "axes": [
      {"pole_a": "X", "pole_b": "Y"}
    ],
    "satellites": [
      {"name": "S1", "weight": 0.98, "rationale": "Why"}
    ],
    "void": [
      {"name": "Not_This", "reason": "Why excluded"}
    ]
  }
}
```

ENCODER (sender):
  1. identify CENTROID (what cannot change?)
  2. weigh SATELLITES (critical .9 vs nice .5?)
  3. define VOID (what is this NOT?)

DECODER (receiver):
  1. ingest JSON/Markdown
  2. generate test case from constraints
  3. check: inside polytope, outside void?

WHY THIS IS κ-ENGINEERING (gemini):
  forces constraint selection
  not "most likely token" but "most structurally sound"
  turns vibes into architecture

───────────────────────────────────

FIRST DELIVERABLE: Σ-LEDGER OUTPUT SPEC

  v0.1 ships: JSON + plaintext format
  
  three blocks (always present):
  
  A) LEDGER
     κ_max, κ_used
     BOUND claims (typed + cost)
     OPEN hypotheses (typed, budgeted)
     
  B) ANSWER
     content with ∴ / ∴? markers attached to claims
     (not vibes)
     
  C) LOSS / DEGRADE / REFUSAL (one if applicable)
     LOST: what was dropped
     DEGRADED: what's missing + why
     ⊘: what / why / what-instead

  why this wins:
    no new infra required
    model-agnostic
    immediately testable
    creates substrate for κ accounting

